I'm really conflicted about what rating to give....the service was 5 star but the food was only 3 stars for me, while I tend to give more weight to food, I will be nice and just average it out to a 4 star review.  I went here last night for my birthday dinner and picked this restaurant because I was craving some Shrimp & Grits, and it was listed on the menu.  I ordered them and out came a cast iron skillet of shrimp and sausage in a tomato sauce, with some grits in a bowl on the side...not what I was expecting!  The tomato sauce was really bland and gave no flavor whatsoever to the shrimp.  The grits were nice and creamy, but nothing special enough to save the dish.  I fished out the sausage, which had a nice heat to it, and just ate that.  The cheddar bacon biscuits on the side were quite good, and I was glad I had them.  I also had the Tomato Ricotta salad to start...I don't think the lettuce was washed very well because about half of the bites tasted like dirt, but I enjoyed the fresh ricotta.  My family enjoyed their food more than me, but I was blown away by the staff's service and concern that I had not gotten enough to eat.  They wanted to bring me another dish and when I declined they even offered to package me up a meal to go, A+ for service!  I declined and opted to order dessert...it was my birthday after all...and when the bill came they had removed both my entre and the dessert!  I will say the white sangria was excellent and the mac & cheese with pancetta was delicious...I would be willing to give Beckett's another try...just not when I am in the mood for shrimp & grits!

